                            <comment id="13468001" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 19:29:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You&apos;re right.  Patch attached to instead init the vars as default, then parse from the uri, and finally allow overriding with env vars.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13474745" author="jeromatron" created="Fri, 12 Oct 2012 02:51:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 to the changes, though don&apos;t we want to expose a way for them to set those variables with standard hadoop config, possibly namespaced with pig?  e.g. cassandra.pig.wide.row?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13474751" author="jeromatron" created="Fri, 12 Oct 2012 02:58:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was looking at 1.1.5 that didn&apos;t yet have the URL location for Cassandra accepting the widerows or use_secondary flags.  That&apos;s in there in the 1.1 branch.&lt;/p&gt;

